ClientInitializer
public static class ClientInitializer.Client_ControlLogic
extends IdolInitializer.Console_ControlLogic
implements Client

Client_ControlLogic manages the console, GUI, and ZUI for a browser Entity. The browser has a zoomable user interface (ZUI), a control panel (GUI), and a text command console. Type 'help' in the console to see a summary of all of the console commands.

_newPosition

private Vector3d _newPosition
the Client's new location as set by the ZUI, the GUI, or the console.

In this implementation, _newPosition acts as a queue of depth 1. It holds the position given to update(Vector3d, Calendar) until handle(Clock.Alarm) processes it.

_newWidth

private Vector3d _newWidth
the Client's new query radius as set by the ZUI, the GUI, or the console.

In this implementation, _newWidth acts as a queue of depth 1. It holds the width given to setWidth(Vector3d) or setWidth(double,double,double) until handle(Clock.Alarm) processes it.

_newTimeLower

private Calendar _newTimeLower
The Client's new lower bound of temporal query as set by the ZUI, GUI, or the console. In this implementation, _newTimeLower acts as a queue of depth 1. It holds the time given to pushTime(int), updateTime(Calendar), or update(Vector3d, Calendar) until handle(Clock.Alarm) processes it.

_newTimeUpper

private Calendar _newTimeUpper
The Client's new upper bound of temporal query as set by the ZUI, GUI, or the console. In this implementation, _newTimeUpper acts as a queue of depth 1. It holds the time given to pushTime(int), updateTime(Calendar), or update(Vector3d, Calendar) until handle(Clock.Alarm) processes it.

_receptorStateListeners

private final HashMap _receptorStateListeners
maps Receptor into FieldListener.

For each Receptor there is a FieldListener that monitors changes in the Receptor's State.

receptorStateChangeIndication(Receptor) consults _receptorStateListeners to obtain the State changes.

receptorReadyIndication(ClientSideFSM) uses addListener(Receptor) to insert a new FieldListener into _receptorStateListeners.

receptorNotReadyIndication(ClientSideFSM) uses removeListener(Receptor) to remove a FieldListener from _receptorStateListeners.

boolean layerinit

updateDirectory

private void updateDirectory(Receptor r,
                             List changes)
Actions for QoS that contains ConsumerViewInterpreter. Schedules the fetching of a Receptor from any new directory entries. Applies changes in the Directory server's state to the AdminPanel of the GUI (if there is one).

Each Field.ChangeMessage in changes contains a HashMap with ServerContact as keys and String as values. The field names are mangled with the name of the ViewInterpreter class.

The contents of Field.ChangeMessages whose names match that of ClientInitializer.ADDED_FIELDNAME are added to the GUI's directory display.

The contents of Field.ChangeMessages whose names match that of ClientInitializer.REMOVED_FIELDNAME are removed from the GUI's directory display.

Parameters:
r - the Receptor from a directory service
changes - a List of Field.ChangeMessage

handleCommand

public final void handleCommand(String command)
Implements comments and the connect, currenttime, gotolatlon, gotolatlonelev, log4j, quit, settime, update, wait, and width commands. Delegates all others to the base class. A comment is any line with '#' as the first non-whitespace character. The commands, their arguments, and their meanings are
  • # - comment
  • connect <serverName> <port> <session> <viewInterpreterClassName> - request a receptor from a server given its name and contact port, a session number, and the fully qualified name of the ViewInterpreter
  • currenttime - prints the current time in milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970.
  • gotolatlon <latitude> <longitude> - Change the position of the view without changing the elevation.
  • gotolatlonelev <latitude> <longitude> <elevation> - Change the position of the viewer.
  • log4j <fully qualified class name> DEBUG|INFO|WARN|ERROR|FATAL - Change the LOG4J logging level of a class.
  • quit - Stop and exit.
  • settime [<time in milliseconds since the epoch>] - Without an argument, set the clock to the current time. With an argument, set the clock to some number of milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970.
  • update <milliseconds> - Change the update rate. A rate less than zero turns off updates.
  • wait <milliseconds> - Don't do anything for a while.
  • width <latitude> <longitude> <elevation> - Set the radius of the spatial search.

Specified by:
handleCommand in interface Console.CommandHandler
Overrides:
handleCommand in class IdolInitializer.Console_ControlLogic
Parameters:
command - a string to interpret as a command
